Seven bomb blasts rocked Jaipur, killing 80 and injuring 200 in a terror attack.
Among the victims were a 10-year-old boy, a bride, and a young man.
The international community, including Pakistan, condemned the violence.
The US, UK, and France expressed solidarity with India.
Jaipur, a top tourist destination, has been targeted before.
Police arrested two suspects after the attacks.
The bombings aimed to sow fear and division, but authorities urged calm.
The US pledged support in India's fight against terrorism.
The city mourns the senseless loss of innocent lives.
